====Concrete Slab Preparation==== 
After clearing the slab site, we started on the slab preparation. We built an 8-foot by 8-foot wooden frame for the concrete slab out of wood and nails found in the shop on site; we made sure that the ground was level for the frame to sit on by using string and a level. We filled the inside of the frame with rock and sand. The frame was designed to create a 4-6 inch slab. The frame was rebared and poured by a local contractor at the same time as a larger concrete driveway was poured at Old Growth Cellars.
